name: sfchronicle
text: PG&E officials said they had “high confidence” that speedy and dry Diablo winds would arrive Wednesday and National Weather Service forecasters were in agreement that “this will be a high risk event.” https://t.co/gGdsPKbVsu

name: sfchronicle
text: As of Tuesday afternoon, areas most likely to lose power include North Bay mountains near Mount St. Helena and Morgan Valley, parts of the East Bay near Mount Diablo, part of the Oakland hills east of Piedmont and high-elevation areas east of Milpitas. https://t.co/gGdsPKbVsu

name: sfchronicle
text: Portions of the mountains around Santa Cruz and Big Sur, as well as the northern Sierra Nevada foothills and high points along the west side of the Sacramento Valley could be affected too.  https://t.co/gGdsPKbVsu
